2 SENATE BILL 641
1 BY adding to
2 Article – State Finance and Procurement
3 Section 11–203(a)(1)(xx) and (b)(5) and 13–218(f)
4 Annotated Code of Maryland
5 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
6 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
7 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
8 Article – State Finance and Procurement
9 11–203.
10 (a) Except as provided in subsection (b) of this section, this Division II does not
11 apply to:
12 (1) procurement by:
13 (xviii) the Department of Natural Resources, for:
14 1. negotiating or entering into grants, agreements, or
15 partnerships with nonprofit entities related to conservation service opportunities; and
16 2. negotiating or entering into pay–for–success contracts in
17 accordance with § 13–112.1 of this Division II; [and]
18 (xix) the State Archives for preservation, conservation, proper care,
19 restoration, and transportation of fine art or decorative art that is:
20 1. in the custody of the Commission on Artistic Property; and
21 2. owned by or loaned to the State; AND
22 (XX) EXCEPT FOR A PROJECT THAT IS SUBJECT TO TITLE 17,
23 SUBTITLE 2 OF THIS ARTICLE, THE DEPARTMENT OF GENERAL SERVICES, THE
24 DEPARTMENT OF HOUSING AND COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT, THE DEPARTMENT
25 OF PLANNING, AND THE DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION FOR NEGOTIATING OR
26 ENTERING INTO AGREEMENTS OR PARTNERSHIPS WITH NONPROFIT ENTITIES FOR
27 PROJECTS RELATED TO HISTORIC PRESERVATION, ARCHAEOLOGY, OR
28 CONSERVATION SERVICE OPPORTUNITIES;
29 (b) (5) SECTION 13–218(F) OF THIS ARTICLE APPLIES TO A CONTRACT
30 DESCRIBED UNDER SUBSECTION (A)(1)(XVIII)1 OR (XX) OF THIS SECTION.
31 13–218.

SENATE BILL 641 3
1 (F) A CONTRACT DESCRIBED UNDER § 11–203(A)(1)(XVIII)1 OR (XX) OF
2 THIS ARTICLE SHALL INCLUDE CLAUSES REQUIRING THE NONPROFIT ENTITY TO:
3 (1) SUBCONTRACT THE PERFORMANCE OF HISTORIC PRESERVATION,
4 ARCHAEOLOGY, AND CONSERVATION SERVICES TO THIRD–PARTY FIRMS;
5 (2) COMPETITIVELY PROCURE ANY SUBCONTRACTED SERVICES IN A
6 TRANSPARENT MANNER IN ACCORDANCE WITH APPLICABLE STATE LAW,
7 INCLUDING THE MINORITY BUSINESS ENTERPRISE REQUIREMENTS UNDER TITLE
8 14, SUBTITLE 3 OF THIS ARTICLE;
9 (2) (3) PROVIDE ANNUAL REPORTS TO THE UNIT ON PARTNERSHIP
10 OUTCOMES AND EXPENDITURES, INCLUDING MINORITY BUSINESS ENTERPRISE
11 SUBCONTRACTING UTILIZATION; AND
12 (3) (4) MAXIMIZE OPPORTUNITIES FOR COMMUNITY ENGAGEMENT
13 RELATED TO THE HISTORIC PRESERVATION, ARCHAEOLOGY, OR CONSERVATION
14 SERVICE OPPORTUNITY.
15 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
16 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
